fields.name: Farm Stand
fields.description: Farm Stands can range from a self-serve refrigerator on the back porch to a full-service store.

fields.name: Farmers Market
fields.description: Farmers Markets are a great way to support local farmers, celebrate our community, and stock your fridge for the week.

fields.name: Agritourism
fields.description: Agritourism is a fun way to explore the rich agricultural landscape of Whatcom County.

fields.name: Organic Farm
fields.description: Organic Farms offer products certified to be free of chemical pesticides, fertilizers, hormones and antibiotics.

fields.name: U-Pick
fields.description: U-Pick is a great way to spend some time outdoors in the country and participate in the harvest. Bring containers, leave pets at home, and wear "grubby" clothes.

fields.name: Food To Bank On
fields.description: Food To Bank On helps beginning farmers get started while they connect with mentor farmers and deliver fresh food to local food banks and shelters.

fields.name: Community Supported Agriculture (CSA)
fields.description: Community Supported Agriculture (CSA) is a convenient and fun way to invest in local agriculture. Typically, a flat fee for membership is paid to the farmer before the season begins, providing spring capital. Members then receive a weekly "subscription" of the freshest items the farm has to offer. CSA programs vary widely in cost, size and content—check listings and call around to find one that fits your needs!

fields.name: Sustainable Connections
fields.description: Sustainable Connections' members are committed to a local economy built on sustainable business practices.

fields.name: Bellingham Green Power
fields.description: Bellingham Green Power purchasers cause 12% of Bellingham's electricity to come from renewable sources: wind, sun, and local cow power!

fields.name: Whatcom Watershed Business Pledge
fields.description: Whatcom Watershed Business Pledge is a voluntary pollution-prevention program to help reduce waste and water pollution.

fields.name: Toward Zero Waste
fields.description: Toward Zero Waste is a business-led, community-wide campaign to reduce waste and increase rates of recycling.

fields.name: Certified Organic
fields.description: Certified Organic identifies products free of chemical pesticides and fertilizers, hormones and preventative antibiotics.

fields.name: Salmon Safe
fields.description: Salmon Safe certification identifies farms using agricultural practices that protect water quality, salmon habitat, and native biodiversity.

fields.name: Food Alliance
fields.description: Food Alliance certification indicates farms with healthy labor practices, pesticide usage, treatment of livestock, and conservation of soil, water and wildlife.

fields.name: Appel Farms
